</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Class Balance</span><hr size=1> But WHO do they listen to ?  The loud but vocal minority or the quiet majority ?  Verant isn't in a enviable position.  No matter what they do, somebody's going to complain, whether they NERF, enchance or do nothing.  <br>
<br>
And just WHAT is balance ?  Are rogues unpowered because they can't solo, or overpowered because of the damage they do ?  Are mages underpowered because they can't do massive damage all the time, or overpowered because with wise chain casting, they can solo something that a group of just plain melees would get wiped out with ( such as a Black Reaver in CoM, I've seen it done by a mage before ) ?  <br>
<br>
There's a lot more to balance than meets the eye, and you can't discount other useful abilities just because you can't do what other classes can.  Each class has their own unique abilities, and it's a shame to hear someone whine about their class, when if they took the time they could see just how great their class is to play. <br>
<br>
Granted some classes have a harder time getting into groups than others, so you'll have to work a bit on your rep and be desired in groups just for that.   Even in places like Sebilis, I'll take the druid I know with a good rep, over a cleric I know to be a jerk, or a necro I knew from way back with as a good group player over the enchanter that I know isn't.  If you're likeable, you WILL eventually get picked for groups a lot no matter what your class.   Balance will always be skewed against people with bad attitudes. <p><img src="http://www.twilite.org/~chrome/images/sigs/larcensig.jpg" border="0">
