<br>
However, raids are way different than exp grouping.  <br>
<br>
On raids, a lot more spells are resisted than normal (and this is even with them reducing the magic resistances on some stuff) which really penalizes how much damage you can do on a mob.  Pets are just a liability and cause more trouble than they are worth - This pentalizes the pet classes b/c they are going to be doing half the damage they normally do.  Various things set raids apart from exp groups.<br>
<br>
However, I think more people would rather themselves balanced so they are wanted in groups (which does include more damage dealing) than being balanced against how much damage another class does.  Every class needs at least one thing that they are wanted for in a group that another class of their type doesn't have.  No one should say, &quot;Gee, we have a rogue, do we really need a ranger?&quot;  IMO if they can't get all classes desirable in groups, they should give the least desirable ones a grouping bonus.  For example, grouping with a Magician increases the amount of exp you get by 3%.<br>
<br>
I also agree with the list above though.  I mean, every company is allowed to have mistakes, but some of the ones Verant has made are just so laughable.  Another thing though is the way Verant chooses to address these issues.  A few people complain for a couple months with no one listening, then more people chime in and more and more and more til finally whatever class board these peopel belong to are just fuming with grief til Verant finally says, &quot;Oh yeah, we finally looked into that and yeah, it is broken!&quot;   <p><div align="Center"><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg" alt="Cantatus - Phantasmist and Artisan of the Karana Server" width="253" height="75">
