<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/24/02 6:44:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqutsemnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qutsemnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/02 3:14:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22386.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thing is</span><hr size=1> My food for thought:<br>
Wizzes port<br>
Necros solo their but off<br>
Mages have no shortage of gimmicks<br>
<br>
My point: the above have entertaining elements above and beyond their DPS.   I mean i told a wiz we didnt have a root parker he reminded me he could do that.  So thats got to come into consideration when talking about how much damage they do.<br>
<br>
A rogue is only DPS.  unless you consider opening locks and sneak hiding to be on par with porting (snarfle)   That has to be considered when &quot;balancing&quot;  Personally i think they just need to get rogues more tricks then they wont bitch about DPS.   More cool and powerful right clicks might do it.  Most fantasy games and novels (D&amp;D for example gave rogues a chance to use wands and scrolls)  have the rogue with trinkets for effect (for a basis).<br>
<br>
Further  the ability to control when and where and how you rage out damage will always be a force multiplier.  That has to be considered in balancing.  ie  if you can pick the minute you do 6k worth of damage but not do any the next minute that will certainly be more valuable then doing 3k a minute.  <br>
<br>
The above isnt true in exp groups you might counter?  Naw it is.  Do guild exp groups.  Most stops to action occur on a nasty pull.  A wiz for example has the ability to end a nasty pull before the healers mana gets eaten to nothing.   In a pickup group sometimes you arnt honed enough to see how a wiz is every bit the equal to a rogue.  if not superior even for exping.  And its because of that principle above: controling damage output is a force multiplier.  (that is you may do less damage over time but it will SEEM like more as far as results)<br>
<br>
What was a saying above:<br>
Rogues need to rock on damage clearly above other classes unless they want to dole out rogues some more non-damage oriented tricks.<br>
<br>
Thats balance.<br>
<br>
